&lt;p&gt;Scale&#39;s Finance Analytics and Data Science team is looking for an experienced data leader to manage a team of analysts and data engineers building internal tools and AI agents that automate workflows across finance and accounting.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role, you will lead a small team while staying technically hands-on, working closely with stakeholders across business finance, corporate finance, and accounting to understand their workflows and build systems that enable faster turnaround times with higher degrees of accuracy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will guide your team in designing data models, prototyping internal tools, and implementing agent-driven workflows using our internal data infrastructure, system integration tooling, Scale&#39;s proprietary AI platform, and emerging AI tools.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for someone who enjoys solving complex problems, building systems from the ground up, translating ambiguous business needs into scalable technical solutions, and developing the people around them.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead and grow a small team of analysts and engineers, providing technical mentorship, career development, and day-to-day guidance&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and develop &lt;strong&gt;end-to-end agent-driven workflows&lt;/strong&gt; that automate finance and accounting processes, and improve operational efficiency&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
